 {"id":"bd-3tf","title":"Add --backup flag for in-place safety","description":"## Purpose
Add a `--backup` flag that creates a backup copy of the original file before in-place editing. This is a critical safety feature that users expect from any file-modifying tool.

## CLI Interface

```bash
# Create backup before in-place edit
aadc -i --backup file.txt
# Creates: file.txt.bak, then edits file.txt

# With custom backup extension
aadc -i --backup --backup-ext .orig file.txt
# Creates: file.txt.orig

# Default: only with -i flag
aadc --backup file.txt  # Error: --backup requires --in-place
```

## Implementation

### Argument Definition (clap)
```rust
#[derive(Parser, Debug)]
pub struct Config {
    // ... existing args ...

    /// Create backup file before in-place editing
    /// 
    /// Creates a copy of the original file with .bak extension
    /// before making any changes. Only valid with --in-place.
    #[arg(long, requires = "in_place")]
    pub backup: bool,

    /// Backup file extension (default: .bak)
    #[arg(long, default_value = ".bak", requires = "backup")]
    pub backup_ext: String,
}
```

### Backup Logic
```rust
fn create_backup(path: &Path, ext: &str) -> anyhow::Result<PathBuf> {
    let backup_path = path.with_extension(
        format!("{}{}", 
            path.extension().map(|e| e.to_str().unwrap_or("")).unwrap_or(""),
            ext
        )
    );

    // More robust: append extension rather than replace
    let mut backup_name = path.as_os_str().to_owned();
    backup_name.push(ext);
    let backup_path = PathBuf::from(backup_name);

    fs::copy(path, &backup_path)
        .with_context(|| format!(
            "Failed to create backup at {}",
            backup_path.display()
        ))?;

    Ok(backup_path)
}
```

### Integration Point
```rust
fn process_file(path: &Path, config: &Config) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    // Create backup BEFORE reading (to preserve exact original)
    if config.in_place && config.backup {
        let backup = create_backup(path, &config.backup_ext)?;
        if config.verbose {
            eprintln!("Created backup: {}", backup.display());
        }
    }

    let content = fs::read_to_string(path)?;
    let result = process_content(&content, config)?;

    if config.in_place {
        fs::write(path, &result)?;
    } else {
        print!("{}", result);
    }

    Ok(())
}
```

## Edge Cases

### 1. Backup Already Exists
```rust
// Option A: Overwrite (current approach)
fs::copy(path, &backup_path)?;

// Option B: Numbered backups (future enhancement)
// file.txt.bak, file.txt.bak.1, file.txt.bak.2, etc.
```

### 2. No Permission to Create Backup
```
Error: Failed to create backup at /path/file.txt.bak: Permission denied
Hint: Ensure write permission in the directory
```

### 3. Disk Full
```
Error: Failed to create backup at /path/file.txt.bak: No space left on device
```

### 4. Network/Remote Filesystems
- Use atomic copy where possible
- Consider temp file approach for better reliability

