 {"id":"bd-b9s","title":"ROBUSTNESS: Error Handling and Edge Case Implementation","description":"## Purpose
Implement comprehensive error handling and edge case management across the aadc codebase to ensure robustness and graceful degradation.

## Error Categories and Handling

### 1. File I/O Errors

#### 1.1 File Not Found
```rust
// When user specifies a file path that doesn't exist
fn process_file(path: &Path) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    if !path.exists() {
        anyhow::bail!("File not found: {}", path.display());
    }
    // ...
}
```

**User-facing message:**
```
Error: File not found: /path/to/diagram.txt
```

#### 1.2 Permission Denied
```rust
fn read_file(path: &Path) -> anyhow::Result<String> {
    fs::read_to_string(path)
        .with_context(|| format!("Cannot read file '{}': permission denied or file locked", path.display()))
}
```

#### 1.3 In-Place Write to Stdin
```rust
// CLI validation: --in-place requires a file argument
fn validate_cli_args(cfg: &Config) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    if cfg.in_place && cfg.file.is_none() {
        anyhow::bail!("--in-place (-i) requires a file argument; cannot edit stdin in place");
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

#### 1.4 Atomic In-Place Writes
```rust
fn write_in_place(path: &Path, content: &str) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    // Write to temp file first, then rename (atomic on most filesystems)
    let temp_path = path.with_extension("tmp");
    fs::write(&temp_path, content)
        .with_context(|| format!("Failed to write temporary file: {}", temp_path.display()))?;

    fs::rename(&temp_path, path)
        .with_context(|| format!("Failed to replace original file: {}", path.display()))?;

    Ok(())
}
```

---

### 2. CLI Argument Errors

#### 2.1 Invalid Score Range
```rust
fn validate_min_score(score: f64) -> anyhow::Result<f64> {
    if !(0.0..=1.0).contains(&score) {
        anyhow::bail!(
            "--min-score must be between 0.0 and 1.0 (got {})",
            score
        );
    }
    Ok(score)
}
```

#### 2.2 Invalid Max Iterations
```rust
fn validate_max_iters(iters: usize) -> anyhow::Result<usize> {
    if iters == 0 {
        anyhow::bail!("--max-iters must be at least 1 (got 0)");
    }
    if iters > 1000 {
        eprintln!("Warning: --max-iters {} is very high; this may slow processing", iters);
    }
    Ok(iters)
}
```

#### 2.3 Invalid Tab Width
```rust
fn validate_tab_width(width: usize) -> anyhow::Result<usize> {
    if width == 0 || width > 16 {
        anyhow::bail!(
            "--tab-width must be between 1 and 16 (got {})",
            width
        );
    }
    Ok(width)
}
```

---

### 3. Input Content Handling

#### 3.1 Empty File
```rust
fn process_content(content: &str) -> String {
    if content.is_empty() {
        // Silently return empty output for empty input
        return String::new();
    }
    // ... normal processing
}
```

#### 3.2 Binary Content Detection
```rust
fn is_likely_binary(content: &[u8]) -> bool {
    // Check first 8KB for null bytes (common binary indicator)
    let check_len = content.len().min(8192);
    content[..check_len].contains(&0)
}

fn process_input(path: &Path) -> anyhow::Result<String> {
    let bytes = fs::read(path)?;
    if is_likely_binary(&bytes) {
        anyhow::bail!(
            "File appears to be binary: {}. aadc only processes text files.",
            path.display()
        );
    }
    String::from_utf8(bytes)
        .with_context(|| format!("File is not valid UTF-8: {}", path.display()))
}
```

#### 3.3 Very Large Files
```rust
const MAX_FILE_SIZE: u64 = 100 * 1024 * 1024; // 100 MB

fn check_file_size(path: &Path) -> anyhow::Result<()> {
    let metadata = fs::metadata(path)?;
    if metadata.len() > MAX_FILE_SIZE {
        anyhow::bail!(
            "File too large ({} MB). Maximum supported size is {} MB.",
            metadata.len() / (1024 * 1024),
            MAX_FILE_SIZE / (1024 * 1024)
        );
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

#### 3.4 Invalid UTF-8
```rust
fn read_as_utf8(path: &Path) -> anyhow::Result<String> {
    let bytes = fs::read(path)?;

    // Try UTF-8 first
    if let Ok(s) = String::from_utf8(bytes.clone()) {
        return Ok(s);
    }

    // Provide helpful error message
    let (valid_up_to, byte_at_error) = {
        match std::str::from_utf8(&bytes) {
            Err(e) => (e.valid_up_to(), bytes.get(e.valid_up_to()).copied()),
            Ok(_) => unreachable!(),
        }
    };

    anyhow::bail!(
        "Invalid UTF-8 at byte position {} (byte value: {:?}). \
         File must be valid UTF-8 text.",
        valid_up_to,
        byte_at_error
    )
}
```

---

### 4. Algorithm Edge Cases

#### 4.1 Lines Longer Than Terminal Width
```rust
// Processing should still work; just won't "fix" lines that exceed target
fn generate_revisions(line: &AnalyzedLine, target_col: usize) -> Vec<Revision> {
    // Skip if line already at or beyond target (monotone edit guarantee)
    if line.suffix_border.as_ref().map(|s| s.col).unwrap_or(0) >= target_col {
        return vec![];  // No revision needed
    }
    // ... normal generation
}
```

#### 4.2 No Diagram Blocks Found
```rust
// Not an error; file is passed through unchanged
fn process_content(content: &str, cfg: &Config) -> ProcessResult {
    let blocks = detect_blocks(content);

    if blocks.is_empty() {
        if cfg.verbose {
            eprintln!("No diagram blocks detected");
        }
        return ProcessResult {
            output: content.to_string(),
            blocks_processed: 0,
            revisions_applied: 0,
        };
    }
    // ...
}
```

#### 4.3 Infinite Loop Prevention
```rust
fn iterative_correction(block: &mut DiagramBlock, cfg: &Config) -> usize {
    let mut iterations = 0;
    let mut prev_state = String::new();

    loop {
        iterations += 1;

        // Safety: max iterations limit
        if iterations > cfg.max_iters {
            if cfg.verbose {
                eprintln!("Warning: Block did not converge after {} iterations", cfg.max_iters);
            }
            break;
        }

        // Safety: detect oscillation (same state as previous)
        let current_state: String = block.lines.iter().map(|l| &l.original).collect();
        if current_state == prev_state {
            // Oscillating; bail out
            break;
        }
        prev_state = current_state;

        // ... apply revisions
    }

    iterations
}
```

---

### 5. Exit Codes

| Code | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| 0 | Success (including no changes made) |
| 1 | General error (file not found, permission denied, etc.) |
| 2 | Invalid CLI arguments |

```rust
fn main() {
    let result = run();
    match result {
        Ok(_) => std::process::exit(0),
        Err(e) => {
            eprintln!("Error: {:#}", e);

            // Determine exit code based on error type
            let code = if e.to_string().contains("not found") 
                       || e.to_string().contains("permission") {
                1
            } else if e.to_string().contains("--") {
                2  // CLI argument error
            } else {
                1
            };

            std::process::exit(code);
        }
    }
}
```

