 {"id":"bd-raz","title":"Add --diff flag for unified diff output","description":"## Purpose
Add a `--diff` flag that outputs changes as a unified diff instead of the full corrected content. Essential for code review, CI pipelines, and understanding exactly what changed.

## CLI Interface

```bash
# Show unified diff of changes
aadc --diff file.txt
# Output: unified diff format (like `diff -u`)

# Combine with dry-run for non-destructive preview
aadc --dry-run --diff file.txt

# Pipe to common tools
aadc --diff file.txt | patch -p0  # Apply changes
aadc --diff file.txt | delta      # Pretty diff viewer
aadc --diff file.txt | colordiff  # Colored output
```

## Implementation

### Dependency
Uses the `similar` crate (already in dependencies) for diff generation.

### Argument Definition (clap)
```rust
#[derive(Parser, Debug)]
pub struct Config {
    // ... existing args ...

    /// Output unified diff instead of full content
    /// 
    /// Shows changes in unified diff format, compatible with
    /// patch, delta, and other diff tools.
    #[arg(long, short = 'd')]
    pub diff: bool,
}
```

### Diff Generation
```rust
use similar::{ChangeTag, TextDiff};

fn print_diff(original: &str, modified: &str, path: &Path) {
    let diff = TextDiff::from_lines(original, modified);

    // Header
    println!("--- {}", path.display());
    println!("+++ {} (corrected)", path.display());

    for (idx, group) in diff.grouped_ops(3).iter().enumerate() {
        // Hunk header
        if let Some(first) = group.first() {
            let old_start = first.old_range().start + 1;
            let new_start = first.new_range().start + 1;
            let old_len = group.iter().map(|op| op.old_range().len()).sum::<usize>();
            let new_len = group.iter().map(|op| op.new_range().len()).sum::<usize>();
            println!("@@ -{},{} +{},{} @@", old_start, old_len, new_start, new_len);
        }

        for op in group {
            for change in diff.iter_inline_changes(op) {
                let (sign, style) = match change.tag() {
                    ChangeTag::Delete => ("-", "red"),
                    ChangeTag::Insert => ("+", "green"),
                    ChangeTag::Equal => (" ", ""),
                };
                print!("{}", sign);
                for (emphasized, value) in change.iter_strings_lossy() {
                    if emphasized {
                        // Could add emphasis styling if using rich_rust
                        print!("{}", value);
                    } else {
                        print!("{}", value);
                    }
                }
                if change.missing_newline() {
                    println!("\n\\ No newline at end of file");
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### Integration with Output Flow
```rust
fn output_result(original: &str, result: &str, config: &Config) {
    if config.diff {
        if original != result {
            print_diff(original, result, config.file.as_ref().unwrap_or(&PathBuf::from("-")));
        } else if config.verbose {
            eprintln!("No changes");
        }
    } else if config.in_place {
        // Write to file
        if let Some(path) = &config.file {
            fs::write(path, result)?;
        }
    } else {
        // Write to stdout
        print!("{}", result);
    }
}
```

## Output Format

### Standard Unified Diff
```diff
--- diagram.txt
+++ diagram.txt (corrected)
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
 +------------------+
-| Short|
+| Short            |
 | Much longer text |
-| Medium|
+| Medium           |
 +------------------+
```

### With Context
```diff
--- README.md
+++ README.md (corrected)
@@ -45,7 +45,7 @@
 Here's my architecture:

 ┌────────────────┐
-│ API Gateway│
+│ API Gateway    │
 │ Authentication │
-│ Rate Limiting│
+│ Rate Limiting  │
 └────────────────┘
```

## Color Support (Future Enhancement)

```rust
// With rich_rust terminal output:
fn print_colored_diff(original: &str, modified: &str, path: &Path, console: &Console) {
    let diff = TextDiff::from_lines(original, modified);

    console.print(&format!("[bold]--- {}[/]", path.display()));
    console.print(&format!("[bold]+++ {} (corrected)[/]", path.display()));

    for change in diff.iter_all_changes() {
        match change.tag() {
            ChangeTag::Delete => console.print(&format!("[red]-{}[/]", change)),
            ChangeTag::Insert => console.print(&format!("[green]+{}[/]", change)),
            ChangeTag::Equal => print!(" {}", change),
        }
    }
}
```

